1
00:00:03,540 --> 00:00:04,881
A guided meditation.

2
00:00:06,323 --> 00:00:14,430
A bell will ring approximately every five minutes and twice after half an hour should you wish to end your meditation then.

3
00:00:17,353 --> 00:00:19,094
So, let us establish the posture.

4
00:00:19,475 --> 00:00:20,435
Lift up the spine.

5
00:00:20,475 --> 00:00:22,018
Remember the puppet string.

6
00:00:22,038 --> 00:00:23,818
Energise but not tense.

7
00:00:25,280 --> 00:00:28,222
And everything else relaxed off the central column.

8
00:00:29,844 --> 00:00:32,146
And the head poised gently on top.

9
00:00:32,701 --> 00:00:51,756
hands on our laps now let's just spend a few moments relaxing first by a mental volition telling all muscles to relax then by tensing and releasing them and finally by deep breathing whatever you feel is necessary to establish calmness in the body

10
00:01:55,507 --> 00:02:00,700
Now, let us acknowledge just noting and observing the feeling of the whole body.

11
00:02:01,763 --> 00:02:05,753
Sitting, sitting, sitting.

12
00:03:07,731 --> 00:03:13,199
Now let us develop the same qualities of alertness and relaxation in the mind using our breath.

13
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:20,288
Note and observe the sensation caused by the process of breathing at your preferred place.

14
00:03:22,072 --> 00:03:26,437
If the mind wanders, just bring it back gently but firmly to the breath.

15
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:32,406
Rising, falling, sitting.

16
00:08:41,249 --> 00:08:49,618
If your mind is wandering, note thinking or dreaming and bring your attention back to the breath, gently but firmly.

17
00:08:50,519 --> 00:08:53,722
If you feel sleepy, put more energy into the spine.

18
00:08:54,403 --> 00:08:56,225
Sit tall but not tense.

19
00:08:59,067 --> 00:09:07,898
By now we should feel more focused and still, so let's open up the awareness and be attentive to whatever comes into the body, mind and heart.

20
00:09:08,754 --> 00:09:15,825
Note and observe carefully any sensations arising at the sense faculties, such as hearing a sound.

21
00:09:16,745 --> 00:09:22,494
Note and observe all sensations in the body, cold and heat, itching, stiffness and so on.

22
00:09:24,176 --> 00:09:28,903
Note and observe all emotional states as and when they occur.

23
00:09:28,942 --> 00:09:37,615
Note and catch all thoughts and images before they lead you astray, and if judging starts up, note it quickly.

24
00:09:40,159 --> 00:09:47,649
Don't be concerned to see the three characteristics of existence, transience, unsatisfactoriness and insubstantiality.

25
00:09:48,490 --> 00:09:57,822
The intuitive intelligence, satipanya, once unlocked from the body, mind and heart, will see these three signs naturally.

26
00:09:58,604 --> 00:10:02,668
If any thought about them occurs, note thinking-thinking.

27
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:07,315
Thought doesn't have the power to make spiritual insight.

28
00:10:09,184 --> 00:10:16,793
So let's just note and observe each physical, mental and emotional event as it arises and passes away.

29
00:10:17,514 --> 00:10:22,539
No need to think about anything, no need to experience something extraordinary.

30
00:10:23,301 --> 00:10:29,307
Just ordinary consciousness and ordinary sensations, thoughts and emotions will do.

31
00:10:31,309 --> 00:10:32,610
Always begin with the breath.

32
00:10:34,072 --> 00:10:37,115
And if we get lost, start again right there.

33
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:43,106
Rising, falling, sitting.

34
00:40:07,519 --> 00:40:12,686
If your mind is wandering, just bring it back gently but firmly to the process of breathing.

35
00:40:13,666 --> 00:40:16,989
If you feel sleepy, sit tall and raise energy up the spine.

36
00:40:18,512 --> 00:40:24,737
Don't be concerned by how many times we've wandered away and have had to re-establish our attentiveness.

37
00:40:25,378 --> 00:40:36,530
This is the practice, this is the training of the mind we must do persistently and patiently, raising interest to see exactly what's happening at the physical, emotional and mental levels.

38
00:40:37,675 --> 00:40:43,382
We keep using the noting technique to tether the mind to all events as they arise and pass away.

39
00:40:44,163 --> 00:40:47,768
And if we get lost, we always start again with the breath.

40
00:40:49,670 --> 00:40:57,221
Once you feel confident, try to meditate without the tape and lengthen your time to a good hour once in the morning and once in the evening.

41
00:40:59,182 --> 00:41:03,528
Don't forget to practice a little loving kindness meditation, metta bhavana.

42
00:41:04,530 --> 00:41:06,012
And when you end the sitting,

43
00:41:06,228 --> 00:41:13,438
Come out slowly and gently and take that satipanya, your intuitive awareness with you, into ordinary daily life.

44
00:41:15,581 --> 00:41:17,764
May your practice bear great fruit.

45
00:41:18,505 --> 00:41:20,708
May you be liberated of all suffering.

46
00:41:21,831 --> 00:41:25,856
May you experience the peace and bliss of Nibbana.
